- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for slot filling. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the proposed approach involves learning semantic representations of slots. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is relevant as slot filling is often used in information retrieval tasks. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is less likely as the paper does not mention any audio or speech-related aspects.
